Mafdet mineral route: sulfur element threat reduction
-1 1 3 0 135 165 3886 7500 6 3800000 0
6745 6746 6749
Mafdet's harbor authority has received damage reports from the first mineral survey expeditions into the Glasswash Fan approach. Sulfur-tolerant acid-seep leeches are corroding equipment in the Dead Pools approach corridors, glasswash sulfur elementals are actively targeting transit personnel, and pumice drifter aggregates are blocking the drainage basin route used for equipment portage. The harbor authority needs one of each engaged and documented before it will authorize further mineral survey operations into the zone.
The sulfur element threat reduction report has been filed and Mafdet's harbor authority has resumed mineral survey operations in the Glasswash approach. Equipment loss reports from the Dead Pools corridor have dropped to zero following the acid-seep leech clearance, and the pumice drifter aggregate blockage in the drainage basin has been broken up sufficiently for equipment portage teams to resume operations. The harbor authority's geological survey contractor has noted the sulfur elemental threat as seasonal and is building a seasonal suppression cost into the next mineral transit licensing contract.
